raw_data.title: Cloud Administrator 1
raw_data.description: Cloud Administrator I, Level 1 is responsible for administrative items such as coordinating meetings, preparing notes, and creating briefing templates.  Work is completed in cloud environments, to include hybrid cloud environments. Maintains and supports the integrity of the operating system environment and various computer systems. May also function in a technical role; Administers, installs and troubleshoots a variety of operating systems, performs systems maintenance tasks, such as system back-up, recovery and file maintenance. Schedules, installs, and tests system software upgrades. Additionally, configures software and resolves technical problems. Monitors and maintains software licensing and maintenance agreements.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: Minimum Education requirement of an Associate's degree may be substituted for 4 years additional experience.

labor_categories.years_experience: Minimum Education requirement of an Associate's degree may be substituted for 4 years additional experience.

raw_data.title: Cloud Consultant IV
raw_data.description: Cloud Consultant IV, Level 4, is responsible for researching and analyzing basic and complex issues surrounding the cloud architectures of an organization including hybrid cloud architectures, SaaS applications, cloud cybersecurity and various Cloud IT systems. Makes recommendations surrounding improving processes, efficiency and practices. Simulates and tests process improvements. Communicates changes and may provide training to impacted business units. Familiar with a variety of the field's concepts, practices, and procedures. Relies on extensive experience and judgment to plan and accomplish goals. Performs a variety of tasks to include systems analysis and implementation. May lead and direct the work of others. A wide degree of creativity and latitude is expected.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: Minimum Education requirement of a Bachelor's degree may be substituted for 8 years additional experience.

labor_categories.years_experience: Minimum Education requirement of a Bachelor's degree may be substituted for 8 years additional experience.

raw_data.title: Cloud Project Manager IV
raw_data.description: Cloud Project Manager IV, Level 4, is responsible for the management of all aspects of a technology project to ensure it is completed on-time and within budget. Has overall responsibility for managing scope, cost, schedule, internal staffing, subcontractors, outside vendors, and contractual deliverable(s). Prepares reports for upper management regarding status of project. Work is completed in cloud environments, to include hybrid cloud environments.  Possesses knowledge of various clouds and/or SaaS technology. Typically reports to a Sr. Program Manager.

raw_data.title: Cloud Subject Matter Expert I
raw_data.description: Cloud Subject Matter Expert (SME) I, Level 2, is responsible for administrative items, analysis of Cloud systems and recommending modifications of Cloud systems.  Work is completed in cloud environments, to include hybrid cloud environments.  May be expected to write documentation to describe logic and corrections. Work is done under supervision, but experience is leveraged to perform higher quality work.  Maintains and supports the integrity of the operating system environment and various computer systems. Administers, installs and troubleshoots a variety of operating systems. performs systems maintenance tasks, such as system back-up, recovery and file maintenance. Schedules, installs, and tests system software upgrades. Additionally, configures software and resolves technical problems. Monitors and maintains software licensing and maintenance agreements.
